Crowd:     14.660, Idrottspark, Norrkoping
Goals:     1-0  Paul Michael Lyons McStay     6'
           2-0  Brian John McClair           17'
           3-0  Gary McAllister              83' penalty
SCOTLAND:  (Manager:  Andrew Roxburgh/52)
Andrew Lewis Goram                (23/Rangers) -
Stewart McKimmie                                    (20/Aberdeen)
Charles (Richard) Gough [c]          (59/Rangers)
David McPherson                           (23/Heart of Midlothian)
Thomas Boyd                                                 (10/Celtic) -
Gary McAllister                                                                      (18/Leeds United)
Paul Michael Lyons McStay                                                                 (60/Celtic)
Stuart McCall                                                                                        (20/Rangers) -
Brian John McClair                                                                                                     (26/Manchester United) 
Kevin William Gallacher                                                                                                                    (12/Coventry City)
Alistair Murdoch McCoist                                                                                                                        (41/Rangers)

Subs:
James Edward McInally                (8/Dundee United)  for Alistair McCoist (67 Minutes)
Patrick Nevin                                             (14/Everton)       for Kevin Gallacher  (79 Minutes)

CIS (Commonwealth of Independent States):  (Coach:  Anatolij Byshovets)
Dmitrij Kharin - Andrej Chernyshov, Oleh Kuznetsov, Kakhaber Tskhadadze, Andrej Kanchelskis - 
Sjarhej Alejnikaw (Dmitrij Kuznetsov 46), Igor Dobrovolskij, Oleksij Mikhajlichenko [c], 
Viktor Onopko - Sergej Kirjakov (Igor Korneev 46), Sergej Juran.

Notes:  The Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS) was a regional organization whose 
        participating countries were former Soviet Republics, formed after the breakup of 
        the Soviet Union in December 1991.
        After this event every independent ex-Soviet nation resumed the use of its Cyrillic 
        alphabet. Since then the full names of some players have been transliterated in 
        different ways according to their place of origin.
        Sjarhej Alejnikaw and Sergej Alejnikov (match 526) are the same player.



